Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.34,0:00:13.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Nearly all religions teach \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.39,0:00:17.31,Default,,0,0,0,,that part of a person survives death.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.31,0:00:19.85,Default,,0,0,0,,But what does the Bible teach?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.85,0:00:24.40,Default,,0,0,0,,God created the first man, Adam, \Nfrom the dust. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.40,0:00:28.45,Default,,0,0,0,,He had the opportunity to live forever. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.45,0:00:31.45,Default,,0,0,0,,But when he deliberately disobeyed God, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.45,0:00:35.04,Default,,0,0,0,,he was told that he would return to the dust\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.03,0:00:38.28,Default,,0,0,0,,—ceasing to exist.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.29,0:00:41.04,Default,,0,0,0,,What about others who died after Adam?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.04,0:00:43.04,Default,,0,0,0,,When Jesus was told \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.04,0:00:45.21,Default,,0,0,0,,that his friend Lazarus died, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.21,0:00:48.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus did not say \Nthat Lazarus had gone to heaven. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.26,0:00:50.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Rather, he said: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.63,0:00:53.68,Default,,0,0,0,,“Our friend has fallen asleep.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.68,0:00:56.00,Default,,0,0,0,,What did he mean?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.02,0:01:01.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Just as someone in a deep sleep \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.85,0:01:05.10,Default,,0,0,0,,is inactive \Nand unaware of his surroundings, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.11,0:01:10.00,Default,,0,0,0,,the dead are not conscious \Nof anything at all.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.45,0:01:15.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Further, just as a person \Ncan be awakened from a deep sleep, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.95,0:01:19.00,Default,,0,0,0,,the Bible shows that it is possible \Nto be awakened from death.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.16,0:01:23.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus did just that \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.12,0:01:26.00,Default,,0,0,0,,for his friend Lazarus.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.42,0:01:32.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Lazarus had been dead for four days. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.68,0:01:35.68,Default,,0,0,0,,If some part of Lazarus \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.68,0:01:38.35,Default,,0,0,0,,had survived his death \Nand gone to heaven, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.35,0:01:40.65,Default,,0,0,0,,would Jesus take him out of heaven \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.64,0:01:43.52,Default,,0,0,0,,and force him to live on earth again? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.52,0:01:45.52,Default,,0,0,0,,No. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.52,0:01:48.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Lazarus was asleep in the grave. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.11,0:01:51.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus gave him back his life \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.19,0:01:54.24,Default,,0,0,0,,and reunited him with his family.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.24,0:01:56.37,Default,,0,0,0,,The Bible promises a time \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.37,0:02:00.00,Default,,0,0,0,,when many people \Nwill be resurrected from the dead, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.99,0:02:02.41,Default,,0,0,0,,just as Lazarus was.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.41,0:02:06.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus spoke of this wonderful hope \Nwhen he said: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.42,0:02:10.59,Default,,0,0,0,,“The one who exercises faith in me, \Neven though he dies, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.59,0:02:13.64,Default,,0,0,0,,will come to life.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.63,0:02:14.92,Default,,0,0,0,,You may wonder: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.93,0:02:17.23,Default,,0,0,0,,‘Who will return to life? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.22,0:02:21.31,Default,,0,0,0,,And what does the resurrection \Ntell us about Jehovah God?’\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.31,0:02:24.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Those questions are answered in lesson 6 \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.52,0:02:27.69,Default,,0,0,0,,of the brochure Good News From God!\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.69,0:02:31.00,Default,,0,0,0,,You can download a copy from jw.org.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.36,0:02:36.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah’s Witnesses would be happy \Nto study the Bible with you.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.61,0:02:39.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Fill in the online request for a Bible study, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.87,0:02:43.63,Default,,0,0,0,,and a Witness in your area \Nwill call to discuss the Bible \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.62,0:02:54.26,Default,,0,0,0,,at a time and place convenient for you.\N
